<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="679" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,776,1878,2063]" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,258,1878,1902]" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[268,333,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Male.</emphasis>
Antennae broken. Antennal flagellum first few segments darker brown and lighter throughout the segments. Head with dark brown stripe running traverse the head. Forewing 
<quantity box="[304,377,1975,1999]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="679" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
and hindwing length 
<quantity box="[602,666,1975,1998]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="679" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
. Forewing pattern as shown (
<figureCitation box="[324,415,2006,2031]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[113,158,1855,1877]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,339,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-80@16.[95,1469,320,1850]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 112–125. Macrostemum hestia. 112, right forewing; Male genitalia: 113, 115, lateral; 114, 116, segment X dorsal; 117, phallus lateral; 118, phallus tip. Macrostemum indistinctum. 119, right forewing; Male genitalia: 120, lateral; 121, segment X dorsal; 122. phallus lateral. Macrostemum luteipes. Male genitalia: 123, lateral; 124, segment X dorsal; 125, phallus lateral. Scale: 112, 119 = 2 mm; 113–118, 120–125 = 0.02 mm (123–125 redrawn from Kimmins, 1955)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5360936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5360936/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum without evident markings. Tibial spurs 2.4.4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[834,1476,189,373]" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,998,189,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Inferior appendages two-segmented. In lateral view, phallus with opening in posterior part of the apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[113,158,1855,1877]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,339,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-80@16.[95,1469,320,1850]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 112–125. Macrostemum hestia. 112, right forewing; Male genitalia: 113, 115, lateral; 114, 116, segment X dorsal; 117, phallus lateral; 118, phallus tip. Macrostemum indistinctum. 119, right forewing; Male genitalia: 120, lateral; 121, segment X dorsal; 122. phallus lateral. Macrostemum luteipes. Male genitalia: 123, lateral; 124, segment X dorsal; 125, phallus lateral. Scale: 112, 119 = 2 mm; 113–118, 120–125 = 0.02 mm (123–125 redrawn from Kimmins, 1955)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5360936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5360936/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Fig. 117</figureCitation>
). In ventral view, phallus apex somewhat heart-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[845,942,285,309]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[113,158,1855,1877]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,339,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-80@16.[95,1469,320,1850]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 112–125. Macrostemum hestia. 112, right forewing; Male genitalia: 113, 115, lateral; 114, 116, segment X dorsal; 117, phallus lateral; 118, phallus tip. Macrostemum indistinctum. 119, right forewing; Male genitalia: 120, lateral; 121, segment X dorsal; 122. phallus lateral. Macrostemum luteipes. Male genitalia: 123, lateral; 124, segment X dorsal; 125, phallus lateral. Scale: 112, 119 = 2 mm; 113–118, 120–125 = 0.02 mm (123–125 redrawn from Kimmins, 1955)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5360936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5360936/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Fig. 118</figureCitation>
). In lateral view, segment X with large wart on apex (
<figureCitation box="[899,1054,317,341]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[113,158,1855,1877]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,339,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-80@16.[95,1469,320,1850]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 112–125. Macrostemum hestia. 112, right forewing; Male genitalia: 113, 115, lateral; 114, 116, segment X dorsal; 117, phallus lateral; 118, phallus tip. Macrostemum indistinctum. 119, right forewing; Male genitalia: 120, lateral; 121, segment X dorsal; 122. phallus lateral. Macrostemum luteipes. Male genitalia: 123, lateral; 124, segment X dorsal; 125, phallus lateral. Scale: 112, 119 = 2 mm; 113–118, 120–125 = 0.02 mm (123–125 redrawn from Kimmins, 1955)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5360936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5360936/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Figs. 113, 115</figureCitation>
). In dorsal view, segment X with longer apex on each side directing sideways (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1418,349,373]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[113,158,1855,1877]" captionTargetBox="[118,1453,339,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-80@16.[95,1469,320,1850]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs. 112–125. Macrostemum hestia. 112, right forewing; Male genitalia: 113, 115, lateral; 114, 116, segment X dorsal; 117, phallus lateral; 118, phallus tip. Macrostemum indistinctum. 119, right forewing; Male genitalia: 120, lateral; 121, segment X dorsal; 122. phallus lateral. Macrostemum luteipes. Male genitalia: 123, lateral; 124, segment X dorsal; 125, phallus lateral. Scale: 112, 119 = 2 mm; 113–118, 120–125 = 0.02 mm (123–125 redrawn from Kimmins, 1955)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5360936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5360936/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Figs. 114, 116</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[835,1475,413,533]" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,927,413,437]" pageId="15" pageNumber="679">Female.</emphasis>
Antennae broken. Antennal flagellum and head markings same as male. Forewing 
<quantity box="[1232,1312,445,469]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="679" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
and hindwing length 
<quantity box="[917,988,477,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="679" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum without evident markings. Tibial spurs 2.4.4.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
